NodeGrid actions don't work correctly with content scale factor (csf) < 1 
(maybe also with csf > 1, I haven't tested this case).
The children of the NodeGrid are partially clipped or, worse, not correctly drawn.
Here the core code snippet ("Liquid" action is only an example, the problem remain with other actions):

```
void HelloWorld::addGridNode() 
{
    auto visibleSize = Director::getInstance()->getVisibleSize();
    auto gridNode = NodeGrid::create();
    gridNode->setPosition(visibleSize * 0.5f);

    auto sprite = Sprite::create("HelloWorld.png");
    gridNode->addChild(sprite);
    addChild(gridNode);

    auto liquid = Liquid::create(5.0, {32, 24}, 5, 8);
    gridNode->runAction(liquid);
}

bool AppDelegate::applicationDidFinishLaunching() {
   ...
    auto director = Director::getInstance();
    director->setContentScaleFactor(0.66f); // or 0.5f, or 1.0f
   ...
}
```

